---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteNav from '../components/SiteNav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import AdSlot from '../components/AdSlot.astro';
import ConvertTool from '../components/tools/ConvertTool.astro';
import siteConfig from '../site.config.ts';

const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'Why convert JPEG to PNG?',
    a: 'The main reasons are: (1) you need to add transparency — JPEG cannot have a transparent background, PNG can; (2) you want a lossless file for editing without further quality loss on re-save; (3) a platform requires PNG specifically; (4) you want to avoid JPEG recompression artefacts when editing and re-saving the image multiple times.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Will the PNG file be larger than the JPEG?',
    a: 'Yes — almost always significantly larger. JPEG uses lossy compression designed for photographs. PNG is lossless — it stores every pixel exactly. A 200 KB JPEG photo may become a 1–3 MB PNG. If file size is a concern and you do not need transparency, keep the JPEG or convert to WebP instead.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Does converting JPEG to PNG improve quality?',
    a: 'No. Any quality loss from the original JPEG encoding is permanent. Converting to PNG saves the current pixel values losslessly, but it cannot recover information discarded during JPEG compression. You get a larger file that will not degrade further when re-saved as PNG — but it is no sharper than the source JPEG.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can I add transparency after converting JPEG to PNG?',
    a: 'This tool converts the JPEG to PNG but does not add or edit transparency. The result is a PNG with the same opaque content as the JPEG. To add transparency (e.g., remove a white background), open the PNG in an image editor like GIMP, Photoshop, or an online background remover after converting.',
  },
  {
    q: 'When should I convert JPEG to PNG for editing?',
    a: 'When you plan to make multiple rounds of edits and saves to the same image. Each JPEG save re-compresses and slightly degrades quality. Working from a PNG master file preserves quality across all edit iterations — then export back to JPEG or WebP when delivering the final version.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is this free and does it upload my image?',
    a: 'Completely free, no account needed, and 100% private. All conversion happens in your browser using the Canvas API. Your JPEG is never uploaded to any server — it is decoded and re-encoded as PNG entirely on your device.',
  },
];

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@graph': [
    {
      '@type': 'WebApplication',
      '@id': `${siteConfig.domain}/jpg-to-png#app`,
      name: 'JPG to PNG Converter Online Free',
      description: 'Convert JPEG to PNG online free. Get a lossless PNG with no further quality loss. No upload, 100% private. For editing, transparency, and design workflows.',
      url: `${siteConfig.domain}/jpg-to-png`,
      applicationCategory: 'MultimediaApplication',
      operatingSystem: 'Any',
      offers: { '@type': 'Offer', price: '0', priceCurrency: 'USD' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'FAQPage',
      mainEntity: faqs.map(({ q, a }) => ({
        '@type': 'Question',
        name: q,
        acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: a },
      })),
    },
  ],
};
---

<Layout
  title="JPG to PNG Converter — Free Online"
  description="Free JPG to PNG converter online. Get a lossless PNG from any JPEG — no further quality loss. No upload, 100% private. For editing, transparency &amp; design."
  canonical={`${siteConfig.domain}/jpg-to-png`}
  keywords="jpg to png, jpeg to png converter, convert jpg to png online, jpg to png free, jpeg png converter"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <SiteNav currentPath="/jpg-to-png" />
  <main class="page-main">
    <div class="tool-screen"><div class="container">
      <header class="tool-header">
        <a href="/" class="back-link">&larr; All tools</a>
        <h1>JPG to PNG Converter — Free</h1>
        <p class="tool-desc">Convert JPEG images to PNG free online. Get a lossless PNG — no further quality loss on re-save. No upload, 100% private. For editing, adding transparency, and design workflows.</p>
      </header>

      <ConvertTool from="JPG" to="png" />

    </div></div>
    <div class="page-spacer" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="page-content"><div class="container">
      <AdSlot slot="1111111111" />

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Convert JPG to PNG — Lossless Editing Master File</h2>
        <p>Converting JPEG to PNG is the standard approach when you need a lossless copy of a photograph for editing. JPEG recompresses the image every time you save — open, adjust, save, open again, adjust, save — causes progressive quality degradation with each cycle. Converting to PNG first gives you a lossless format that preserves the exact pixel values regardless of how many times you re-save it, making it ideal as a working or master file during photo editing projects.</p>
        <p>PNG is also required for images that will be given a transparent background. If you have a product photo in JPEG and need to remove the background to place the product on a different colour or pattern, you need a PNG — JPEG does not support transparent pixels. The correct workflow is: convert JPEG to PNG here, then open the PNG in a background removal tool or image editor to add transparency.</p>
        <p>Note that the PNG output will be substantially larger than the JPEG source. For a typical smartphone photograph, the PNG can be 5–10 times larger. This is normal and expected — PNG's lossless compression stores all pixel data precisely. When you have finished editing, re-save the final version as JPEG or WebP for sharing, uploading, or web delivery.</p>
        <p>This converter works entirely in your browser. Your JPEG is decoded by the browser, drawn onto an HTML5 Canvas, and re-encoded as a lossless PNG. Nothing is uploaded to any server — instant, private, and free.</p>

        <h3>How to Convert JPG to PNG</h3>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Upload your JPEG.</strong> Click "Choose File" or drag and drop your .jpg or .jpeg image.</li>
          <li><strong>PNG is pre-selected.</strong> No format change needed.</li>
          <li><strong>Click "Convert".</strong> The JPEG is decoded and re-encoded as a lossless PNG.</li>
          <li><strong>Download the PNG.</strong> Open it in Photoshop, GIMP, Figma, or your preferred editing tool. Edit freely — each re-save will not degrade the image quality.</li>
          <li><strong>Export when done.</strong> When editing is complete, export back to JPEG or WebP for the final deliverable.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Common Use Cases</h3>
        <p><strong>Background removal:</strong> Remove a white or solid background from a product photo. Convert JPEG to PNG, then use a background removal tool. The transparent PNG can be placed on any background or used in design layouts.</p>
        <p><strong>Multi-step editing:</strong> Working in GIMP or an older version of Photoshop on a file you will open, edit, and re-save many times? Start from PNG to avoid cumulative JPEG artefacts across saves.</p>
        <p><strong>Platform requirements:</strong> Some design platforms, CMS systems, and document tools specifically accept PNG and not JPEG. Convert here to meet those requirements.</p>
      </section>

      <AdSlot slot="2222222222" />

      <section class="faq-section">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <dl class="faq-list">
          {faqs.map(({ q, a }) => (
            <div class="faq-item">
              <dt class="faq-q">
                <button type="button" aria-expanded="false" class="faq-toggle">
                  {q}<span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
                </button>
              </dt>
              <dd class="faq-a" hidden><p>{a}</p></dd>
            </div>
          ))}
        </dl>
      </section>

      <section class="related-section">
        <h2>Related Tools</h2>
        <div class="related-grid">
          <a href="/png-to-jpg" class="related-card">
            <span class="related-name">PNG to JPG</span>
            <span class="related-desc">Smallest file for photos</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/jpg-to-webp" class="related-card">
            <span class="related-name">JPG to WebP</span>
            <span class="related-desc">25–34% smaller for web</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/compress-image" class="related-card">
            <span class="related-name">Compress Image</span>
            <span class="related-desc">Reduce file size in KB</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/webp-to-png" class="related-card">
            <span class="related-name">WebP to PNG</span>
            <span class="related-desc">Convert WebP to lossless</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div></div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<script is:inline>
  document.querySelectorAll('.faq-toggle').forEach(function(btn) {
    btn.addEventListener('click', function() {
      var expanded = btn.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';
      btn.setAttribute('aria-expanded', String(!expanded));
      var dd = btn.closest('.faq-item').querySelector('.faq-a');
      var icon = btn.querySelector('.faq-icon');
      dd.hidden = expanded;
      if (icon) icon.textContent = expanded ? '+' : '−';
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  .page-main { padding: 0; }
  .tool-screen { position: fixed; top: 64px; left: 0; right: 0; height: calc(100vh - 64px); overflow-y: auto; background: var(--site-bg); z-index: 1; padding: 2rem 0 1.5rem; }
  .page-spacer { height: 100vh; }
  .page-content { position: relative; z-index: 2; background: var(--site-bg); padding: 2rem 0 4rem; }
  .container { max-width: 860px; margin-inline: auto; padding-inline: 1.5rem; }
  .tool-header { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .back-link { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.375rem; font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--site-text-muted); text-decoration: none; margin-bottom: 1rem; transition: color 0.15s; }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--site-text); text-decoration: none; }
  h1 { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2rem); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -1.28px; color: var(--site-text); line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 0.75rem; }
  .tool-desc { font-size: 1.0625rem; color: var(--site-body); margin: 0; max-width: 64ch; line-height: 1.6; }
  .content-section { margin: 2.5rem 0; }
  .content-section h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.96px; color: var(--site-text); margin: 0 0 0.75rem; }
  .content-section h3 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.6px; color: var(--site-text); margin: 1.75rem 0 0.5rem; }
  .content-section p { color: var(--site-body); margin: 0 0 1rem; max-width: 72ch; line-height: 1.6; }
  .content-section ol { color: var(--site-body); padding-left: 1.5rem; max-width: 64ch; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  .content-section li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; line-height: 1.6; }
  .faq-section { margin: 2.5rem 0; }
  .faq-section h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.96px; color: var(--site-text); margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
  .faq-list { margin: 0; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .faq-item { border: 1px solid var(--site-border); border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden; }
  .faq-toggle { width: 100%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 0.75rem; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; background: var(--site-bg-card); border: none; color: var(--site-text); font-size: 0.9375rem; font-weight: 600; text-align: left; cursor: pointer; transition: background 0.15s; }
  .faq-toggle:hover { background: var(--site-hover); }
  .faq-icon { font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1; flex-shrink: 0; color: var(--site-text-muted); }
  .faq-a { margin: 0; padding: 0 1.25rem 1rem; background: var(--site-bg-card); }
  .faq-a p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--site-text-muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .related-section { margin: 2rem 0; }
  .related-section h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.6px; color: var(--site-text); margin: 0 0 0.875rem; }
  .related-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(175px, 1fr)); gap: 0.625rem; }
  .related-card { display: block; padding: 0.875rem 1rem; border: 1px solid var(--site-border); border-radius: 8px; text-decoration: none; background: var(--site-bg-card); transition: box-shadow 0.15s, border-color 0.15s; }
  .related-card:hover { box-shadow: var(--shadow-2); border-color: var(--site-border-strong); text-decoration: none; }
  .related-name { display: block; font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--site-text); margin-bottom: 0.2rem; }
  .related-desc { display: block; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--site-text-muted); line-height: 1.4; }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .page-content { padding: 1.5rem 0 3rem; }
    h1 { letter-spacing: -0.5px; }
    .content-section h2, .faq-section h2 { letter-spacing: -0.4px; }
    .content-section { margin: 1.75rem 0; }
    .faq-section { margin: 1.75rem 0; }
  }
</style>
